5:
Hey, everyone... I'd like to go to a
casino!
14:
Say no more, I'm in! You've never
been, right? I can't miss out on your
first time!
18:
I want to go there to enjoy myself,
but... the thing is...
20:
What I really want is to make
money! To pay for my living
expenses.
31:
Are you sure? Not to turn on a dime
here, but uh, this could go wrong
real fast!
36:
You don't need to worry, Pythica. I'm
going to get this right!
43:
Did you see that fire in her eyes? I
say we let her cook.
47:
Indeed. This may even prove to be a
fruitful endeavor for her.
52:
I expected you of all people to be
against going to the casino, Light!
55:
Failure is a quintessential part of life.
If she learns what it means here, she
may learn a valuable lesson.
60:
That's one I can teach her. Kid's
gotta learn at some point that there
are fights you just can't win—not
without experience.
68:
Nooo! I keep LOSING! I just can't get
the hang of this!
77:
I'm not having any luck either... At
this rate, I'm going to be in the red.
81:
I hope this was an eye-opening
experience for you, Echo. To truly
earn a living, one must employ
more—
89:
That was just a warm-up. Now, I'm
going to get serious!
95:
Damn it! I can't catch a break! If I
don't pay back what I owe, they're
gonna kill me...
98: All right! I finally found someone!
102:
W-wait, Echo! Just what are you
planning to do?
106:
Um. I was planning on lending that
man some money and charging
him very high interest.
109:
People like him are always in debt,
right?
112:
They always have to get loans to
pay back their outstanding debt. So,
if I loan them money and charge a
mega high fee, I can make a huge
profit!
122:
I learned that from a tutor I once
had. It's my first time actually trying
it out, though...
126:
But I'm sure I'll succeed. I have to. So
I can make a living on my own!
132:
Now HOLD ON just a moment!
Everything about this is insane!
136:
And to think you considered yourself
a "weak" person!
140:
D-did I say something wrong? Do
you think I should try to be a
pawnbroker instead?
146:
No! Both of those are out of the
question!
153:
P-pardon me. Here are your grilled
seafood noodles.
157:
Thank you very much. Please come
again!
161:
Nice stuff! I'd say you're a perfect fit
for the service industry!
164:
I'm very grateful to hear you say
that, but I'm afraid I still get flustered
when multiple orders come in at
once...
167:
That's okay! Either way, it beats
being a loan shark, doesn't it?
171:
I'm very sorry about that. I really
didn't know that it was a
disreputable profession...
174:
If it hadn't been everyone's
intervention, I might have gone and
done something awful!
177:
To tell you the truth, I honestly kind
of wanted to see it! Imagine you,
bright smile and all, pulling off some
tricky mafia moves. Hehe.
182:
Still, Zantetsu got that shady lender
in the end, right? And that young
man got his debt wiped clean!
Sounds like a happy ending to me!
186:
Haha... It was another reminder of
just how strong you all are.
Experience really makes the
difference, obvious though it is to
say it.
190:
Yeah, they're all really something
else. Not your average Joes, that's
for sure.
194:
Honestly, it gets to me sometimes!
Like, I just wanna be as good as
them, you know?
198:
I didn't know you felt that way too,
Yuna.
202:
I mean, of course! Who wouldn't?
Those guys are really amazing.
206:
But so are you! I mean, I couldn't
hold a candle—
210:
Ah, sorry. I really shouldn't compare.
Our situations are probably very
different.
214:
Hmm, maybe. But you know what? I
think it's okay to have ourselves a
pity party from time to time!
218:
Whatever keeps your spirits up—and
I'd say yours look pretty high right
now!
222:
They are. It's because I've gotten to
learn so much, and because of how
much you've looked after me.
224:
You really are a kind, wonderful
person, Yuna.
228:
Whaat? Boy, not sure what I did to
deserve praise like that!
232:
Um... If it's okay, I'd really like to talk
with you more.
237:
Of course it's okay! Let's hang out
again after I finish my shift!
242:
Welcome, welcome! Please help
yourselves to a seat!
